nt, England, United Kingdom","Bearsted, Kent, England":"Bearsted, Kent, England","Kent, England":"Kent, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1508–27 March 1572":"van 11 januari 1508 to 10 januari 1509–6 april 1572","1508–1572":"van11januari1508to10januari1509–1572","–Female":"Overleden","1525–Female":"1525–Overleden","1550–1594":"1550–1594","1508–1575":"van11januari1508to10januari1509–1575","1525":"1525","6 May 1572":"16 mei 1572","1575":"1575","1550":"1550","1594":"1594","1572":"1572","27 March 1572":"6 april 1572","1508":"van 11 januari 1508 to 10 januari 1509","Bearstead, Kent, England":"Bearstead, Kent, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Bearsted, Kent, England":"Bearsted, Kent, England","Kent, England":"Kent, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1508–27 March 1572":"from 11 January 1508 to 10 January 1509–6 April 1572","1508–1572":"from11January1508to10January1509–1572","–Female":"Deceased","1525–Female":"1525–Deceased","1550–1594":"1550–1594","1508–1575":"from11January1508to10January1509–1575","1525":"1525","6 May 1572":"16 May 1572","1575":"1575","1550":"1550","1594":"1594","1572":"1572","27 March 1572":"6 April 1572","1508":"from 11 January 1508 to 10 January 1509","Bearstead, Kent, England":"Bearstead, Kent, England, United Kingdom","Bearsted, Kent, England":"Bearsted, Kent, England","Kent, England":"Kent, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Betts","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Bett  , with excrescent <i>-s</i>, a patronymic or metronymic from the medieval personal name <i>Bett</i>, a short form of <i>Bartholomew</i>, <i>Beatrice</i>, or <i>Elizabeth</i>.","Americanized form of German   Betz  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Bettis","meanings":["English: variant of   Betts   (see also   Bett  ), or possibly a topographic name meaning ‘(dweller) by the hollows’, from Old English <i>bytt</i> ‘butt, cask, flagon, womb’, used topographically like Old English <i>byden</i> ‘butt’ (compare   Bidwell  )."]},{"name":"Bett","meanings":["English (Lincolnshire): from the Middle English personal name <i>Bett(e)</i>. When feminine it was usually a pet form of <i>Beatrice</i> but possibly also <i>Elizabeth</i>. When masculine it was a pet form of <i>Bertram</i> or <i>Bertelmew</i> (see   Bartholomew  )."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Betts was born from 11 January 1508 to 10 January 1509, in Bearstead, Kent, England, United Kingdom as the son of Thomas Betts. He had at least 1 son with Agnes Teyre. He died on 6 April 1572, in his hometown, and was buried in Kent, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1508–27 March 1572":"11. jaanuar 1508 kuni 10. jaanuar 1509–6. aprill 1572","1508–1572":"11.jaanuar1508kuni10.jaanuar1509–1572","–Female":"Surnud","1525–Female":"1525–Surnud","1550–1594":"1550–1594","1508–1575":"11.jaanuar1508kuni10.jaanuar1509–1575","1525":"1525","6 May 1572":"16. mai 1572","1575":"1575","1550":"1550","1594":"1594","1572":"1572","27 March 1572"